data.title: The Lives and Times of Cambodia's Sihanouk (1996)
data.meta_description: King Norodom Sihanouk looks back over the past 50 years of Cambodia's tumultuous history and his own privotal role in the fate of his people before, during and after 'The Killing Fields'. Part 2 focuses on the rise of Hun Sen, Cambodia's new strongman, to challenge the pre-eminence of the aging King Sihanouk.
data.text:
King Norodom Sihanouk looks back over the past 50 years of Cambodia's tumultuous history and his own privotal role in the fate of his people before, during and after 'The Killing Fields'. Part 2 focuses on the rise of Hun Sen, Cambodia's new strongman, to challenge the pre-eminence of the aging King Sihanouk.
